{"TopicId":167158,"ForumId":44,"TopicTitle":"Serious Scientific Answers to Absurd Hypothetical questions","CreatedByName":"DAL59","CreatedById":180784,"CreatedDateTime":"2017-11-03T20:21:11Z","PageNum":22,"Articles":[{"CreatedByName":"Gargamel","CreatedById":64714,"CreatedDateTime":"2018-09-24T23:56:57Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223457038\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022167158\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221537800593\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022182951\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022KG3\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n9 hours ago, KG3 said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nwhile the exterior is made of pine;\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nWhich is really unsuitable for a ship of this design.\u00A0 Yes, you can use it, it will work, but it won\u0027t last that long.\u00A0 I\u0027m a woodworker, not a wooden ship builder (I do build CF and plastic hulled boats though), so there may be processes that make pine usable, but there are many other hard woods available (pine is a soft wood) that are far more suitable for ship building.\u00A0\u00A0 But they cost more, and will drive up the price.\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Cheif Operations Director","CreatedById":183218,"CreatedDateTime":"2018-09-25T00:59:29Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nUsing earths magnetic field (in the van Allen belts) to help levitate a ship\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"KG3","CreatedById":182951,"CreatedDateTime":"2018-09-25T02:03:07Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223457053\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022167158\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221537802841\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022107381\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Green Baron\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n10 hours ago, Green Baron said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0And prices for modern day yachts in all sizes including the ones from the rich and super rich are freely available. Without \u0022special equipment\u0022 and crew, i you know what i mean ...\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nGot to love yacht racing.\u00A0 Just owning a racing yacht gets you ranked in the worlds top 50!\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Arugela","CreatedById":133381,"CreatedDateTime":"2018-09-25T13:16:11Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223210258\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022167158\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221509740471\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022180784\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022DAL59\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\nOn 11/3/2017 at 4:21 PM, DAL59 said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nBased on xkcd\u0027s What If(apparently inactive).\u00A0 Ask a absurd hypothetical question, and someone can come and give you a serious scientific answer.\u00A0\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nTechnically this is not true. The only absolutely correct scientific answer is always, \u0022I don\u0027t know.\u0022 Anyone saying anything else is full of you know what.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Cheif Operations Director","CreatedById":183218,"CreatedDateTime":"2018-09-25T22:45:45Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223457517\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022167158\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221537881371\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022133381\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Arugela\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n9 hours ago, Arugela said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nTechnically this is not true. The only absolutely correct scientific answer is always, \u0022I don\u0027t know.\u0022 Anyone saying anything else is full of you know what.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nNot nessicary Gravity is real What if someone asked why things fall\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Mad Rocket Scientist","CreatedById":139256,"CreatedDateTime":"2018-09-26T03:59:10Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223457849\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022167158\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221537915545\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022183218\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Cheif Operations Director\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n5 hours ago, Cheif Operations Director said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nNot nessicary Gravity is real What if someone asked why things fall\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Ca href=\u0022https://xkcd.com/1489/\u0022 rel=\u0022external nofollow\u0022\u003Ehttps://xkcd.com/1489/\u003C/a\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nAlt-text: \u0022Of these four forces, there\u0027s one we don\u0027t really understand.\u0022 \u0022Is it the weak force or the strong--\u0022 \u0022It\u0027s gravity.\u0022\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nAlthough we can say, with 100% accuracy, that we describe the phenomenon that makes things fall down\u00A0as gravity. So gravity does exist, as much as anything does, but there aren\u0027t any guarantees about our models for it being accurate, or describing some kind of deeper truth.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"kerbiloid","CreatedById":129408,"CreatedDateTime":"2018-09-26T04:27:23Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223457980\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022167158\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221537934350\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022139256\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Mad Rocket Scientist\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n28 minutes ago, Mad Rocket Scientist said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nAlthough we can say, with 100% accuracy, that we describe the phenomenon that makes things fall down\u00A0as gravity.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nIf take the observer as the reference point, that\u0027s the Earth gets attracted to him, jumps up, and hits from below every time he tries to push it away, lol.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nAlso, the observer\u0027s car rotates the Earth with its wheels.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222018-09-26T04:27:54Z\u0022 title=\u002209/26/2018 04:27  AM\u0022 data-short=\u00225 yr\u0022\u003ESeptember 26, 2018\u003C/time\u003E by kerbiloid\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Vanamonde","CreatedById":27914,"CreatedDateTime":"2018-09-29T02:36:21Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThe thread went off topic a while back and veered into epistemology and religion. We\u0027ve removed those posts so please get back to asking silly questions and giving serious answers.\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Spaceception","CreatedById":152800,"CreatedDateTime":"2018-09-29T02:53:16Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nDoes it really make sense for wormholes to be automatically \u0022connected\u0022 (is the area between wormholes a different kind of \u0022space\u0022?), and could there instances where you end up in a totally different system than where you intended to go? I know this can\u0027t really be \u0027known\u0027 so what are your thoughts/opinions?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Diche Bach","CreatedById":76097,"CreatedDateTime":"2018-10-12T15:53:32Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nWould it be possible to create a technology that allowed a space craft to \u0022surf\u0022 on a coronal mass ejection?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Gargamel","CreatedById":64714,"CreatedDateTime":"2018-10-12T17:53:36Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223466543\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022167158\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221539359612\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u002276097\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Diche Bach\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n1 hour ago, Diche Bach said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nWould it be possible to create a technology that allowed a space craft to \u0022surf\u0022 on a coronal mass ejection?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nYes.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Diche Bach","CreatedById":76097,"CreatedDateTime":"2018-10-13T02:47:18Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nHmmm . . .\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\nQuote\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cspan style=\u0022background-color:#ffffff;color:#222222;font-size:14px;\u0022\u003ECoronal mass ejections reach velocities from 20 to 3,200\u00A0km/s (12 to 1,988\u00A0mi/s) with an average speed of 489\u00A0km/s (304\u00A0mi/s), based on\u003Cspan\u003E\u00A0\u003C/span\u003E\u003C/span\u003E\u003Ca href=\u0022https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Solar_and_Heliospheric_Observatory\u0022 rel=\u0022external nofollow\u0022 style=\u0022color:#0b0080;font-size:14px;\u0022 title=\u0022Solar and Heliospheric Observatory\u0022\u003ESOHO\u003C/a\u003E\u003Cspan style=\u0022background-color:#ffffff;color:#222222;font-size:14px;\u0022\u003E/\u003C/span\u003E\u003Ca href=\u0022https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/LASCO_Large_Angle_and_Spectrometric_Coronagraph\u0022 rel=\u0022external nofollow\u0022 style=\u0022color:#0b0080;font-size:14px;\u0022 title=\u0022LASCO Large Angle and Spectrometric Coronagraph\u0022\u003ELASCO\u003C/a\u003E\u003Cspan style=\u0022background-color:#ffffff;color:#222222;font-size:14px;\u0022\u003E\u003Cspan\u003E\u00A0\u003C/span\u003Emeasurements between 1996 and 2003. These speeds correspond to transit times from the Sun out to the mean radius of Earth\u0027s orbit of about 13 hours to 86 days (extremes), with about 3.5 days as the average. The average mass ejected is 1.6\u003C/span\u003E\u003Cspan style=\u0022background-color:#ffffff;color:#222222;font-size:14px;\u0022\u003E\u00D7\u003C/span\u003E\u003Cspan style=\u0022background-color:#ffffff;color:#222222;font-size:14px;\u0022\u003E10\u003C/span\u003E\u003Csup style=\u0022background-color:#ffffff;color:#222222;font-size:11.2px;\u0022\u003E12\u003C/sup\u003E\u003Cspan style=\u0022background-color:#ffffff;color:#222222;font-size:14px;\u0022\u003E\u00A0kg (3.5\u003C/span\u003E\u003Cspan style=\u0022background-color:#ffffff;color:#222222;font-size:14px;\u0022\u003E\u00D7\u003C/span\u003E\u003Cspan style=\u0022background-color:#ffffff;color:#222222;font-size:14px;\u0022\u003E10\u003C/span\u003E\u003Csup style=\u0022background-color:#ffffff;color:#222222;font-size:11.2px;\u0022\u003E12\u003C/sup\u003E\u003Cspan style=\u0022background-color:#ffffff;color:#222222;font-size:14px;\u0022\u003E\u00A0lb). However, the estimated mass values for CMEs are only lower limits, because coronagraph measurements provide only two-dimensional data.\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nSeems a lot better than what we have managed so far.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI\u0027ve got our best controlled speed achieved so far as being the Juno probe which achieved 76 km/sec, so 3200 km/sec ~42 times faster. Seems that would still put a one way trip time to Alpha Centauri around the 4,000 years ballpark. Lots better than the 168,000 years it would take a \u0022Juno speed\u0022 spacecraft, but still not very practical.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nOnce again: nuclear pulse propulsion seems to be the only real hope . . .\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222018-10-13T02:48:02Z\u0022 title=\u002210/13/2018 02:48  AM\u0022 data-short=\u00225 yr\u0022\u003EOctober 13, 2018\u003C/time\u003E by Diche Bach\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003Cbr\u003Enuka pulse\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Spaceception","CreatedById":152800,"CreatedDateTime":"2018-10-13T03:23:01Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223466837\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022167158\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221539398838\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u002276097\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Diche Bach\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n31 minutes ago, Diche Bach said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nOnce again: nuclear pulse propulsion seems to be the only real hope . . .\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv\u003E\n\u003Cdiv\u003E\n\u003Cdiv title=\u0022Protected by Grammarly\u0022\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nOnly way I can see us doing that is if someone like Musk or Bezo\u0027s figures out how to get around the outer space treaty/nuclear test ban treaty, and builds it in space, far from Earth. But by the time we\u0027re capable of that, I\u0027d hazard a guess to say we\u0027d have access to something better. That 2013 design for a fusion engine seemed promising, and would lead to more powerful drives, whatever happened to that?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"KG3","CreatedById":182951,"CreatedDateTime":"2018-10-13T04:12:33Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223466847\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022167158\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221539400981\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022152800\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Spaceception\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n44 minutes ago, Spaceception said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nOnly way I can see us doing that is if someone like Musk or Bezo\u0027s figures out how to get around the outer space treaty/nuclear test ban treaty,...\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nDoes the intended use of the device get taken into consideration?\u00A0 After all, if you put a pint of petrol in a bottle with rag stuffed into it you have a bomb.\u00A0 If instead you put the same petrol in the fuel tank of your car you have fuel.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"DAL59","CreatedById":180784,"CreatedDateTime":"2018-10-13T04:22:01Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223466543\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022167158\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221539359612\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u002276097\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Diche Bach\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n12 hours ago, Diche Bach said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nWould it be possible to create a technology that allowed a space craft to \u0022surf\u0022 on a coronal mass ejection?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nWasn\u0027t that in one of the HGTTG books?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Diche Bach","CreatedById":76097,"CreatedDateTime":"2018-10-13T13:33:38Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nWell even with the question of propulsion set aside, I\u0027d say we are decades if not a century from any serious prospects of interstellar. Any vessel of any size will have be assembled in space and clearly we need something a lot more substantial than the ISS for something like that.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Spaceception","CreatedById":152800,"CreatedDateTime":"2018-10-13T14:09:13Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223466865\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022167158\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221539403953\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022182951\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022KG3\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n9 hours ago, KG3 said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nDoes the intended use of the device get taken into consideration?\u00A0 After all, if you put a pint of petrol in a bottle with rag stuffed into it you have a bomb.\u00A0 If instead you put the same petrol in the fuel tank of your car you have fuel.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nYeah, but this is nuclear pulse propulsion you\u0027re talking about. A spacecraft that uses at least thousands of nukes onboard for propulsion. Some early designs were for the military for massive battleships. There would be worries about military contracts for that technology. No matter your intentions, people would be wary, and I wouldn\u0027t be surprised if it quickly became an international matter. Getting permission to build even one ship would be a tremendous undertaking.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223467030\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022167158\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221539437618\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u002276097\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Diche Bach\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n36 minutes ago, Diche Bach said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nWell even with the question of propulsion set aside, I\u0027d say we are decades if not a century from any serious prospects of interstellar. Any vessel of any size will have be assembled in space and clearly we need something a lot more substantial than the ISS for something like that.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nTrue. Plus, we would need a lot of research on autonomous spacecraft, that can make smart decisions, and work properly for decades, or centuries. And spacecraft that can last a very long time without breaking down, or at least, can repair themselves.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222018-10-13T14:09:52Z\u0022 title=\u002210/13/2018 02:09  PM\u0022 data-short=\u00225 yr\u0022\u003EOctober 13, 2018\u003C/time\u003E by Spaceception\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"magnemoe","CreatedById":57801,"CreatedDateTime":"2018-10-13T15:32:56Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223466865\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022167158\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221539403953\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022182951\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022KG3\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n11 hours ago, KG3 said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cspan\u003E\uFEFF\u003C/span\u003E Does the intended use of the device get taken into consideration?\u00A0 After all, if you put a pint of petrol in a bottle with rag stuffed into it you have a bomb.\u00A0 If instead you put the same petrol in the fuel tank of your car you have fuel.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nYou could probably name it an propellant unit and claim its not an bomb because some design, like you could design like it has no power source but it passes trough an magnetic field who gives it power, if it don\u0027t fire it would be inert.\u00A0\u003Cbr\u003E\nNow letting someone holding tons of weapon grade plutonium on the other hand is way more sensitive.\u00A0\u003Cbr\u003E\u003Cbr\u003E\nAnd yes orion would be perfect for moving asteroids around, its pretty much the only realistic design for this.\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Bill Phil","CreatedById":127797,"CreatedDateTime":"2018-10-13T15:53:28Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223467074\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022167158\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221539444776\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u002257801\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022magnemoe\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n19 minutes ago, magnemoe said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nYou could probably name it an propellant unit and claim its not an bomb because some design, like you could design like it has no power source but it passes trough an magnetic field who gives it power, if it don\u0027t fire it would be inert.\u00A0\u003Cbr\u003E\nNow letting someone holding tons of weapon grade plutonium on the other hand is way more sensitive.\u00A0\u003Cbr\u003E\u003Cbr\u003E\nAnd yes orion would be perfect for moving asteroids around, its pretty much the only realistic design for this.\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nWell, mass drivers could move some big stuff around too, though on a smaller time scale.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"kerbiloid","CreatedById":129408,"CreatedDateTime":"2018-10-14T12:58:25Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223466847\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022167158\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221539400981\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022152800\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Spaceception\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\nOn 10/13/2018 at 6:23 AM, Spaceception said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nOnly way I can see us doing that is if someone like Musk or Bezo\u0027s figures out how to get around the outer space treaty/nuclear test ban treaty, and builds it in space, far from Earth.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsSpoiler\u0022 data-ipsspoiler=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsSpoiler_header\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cspan\u003ESpoiler\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsSpoiler_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cimg alt=\u0022korea_pix_2_fixed.jpg?itok=YlMZ25fj\u0022 class=\u0022ipsImage\u0022 height=\u0022480\u0022 src=\u0022http://www1.cbn.com/sites/default/files/styles/image_xl_640x480/public/korea_pix_2_fixed.jpg?itok=YlMZ25fj\u0022 width=\u0022640\u0022\u003E\u003Cimg alt=\u0022a9POE31_700bwp.webp\u0022 class=\u0022ipsImage\u0022 height=\u0022337\u0022 src=\u0022https://img-9gag-fun.9cache.com/photo/a9POE31_700bwp.webp\u0022